# Force LF line endings for everything in this repo, regardless of the
# platform a contributor edits on (Windows/macOS/Linux). This driver is
# built and run on a Raspberry Pi: a CRLF-terminated run.sh fails there
# with "run.sh: line 1: $'\r': command not found" / "bad interpreter"
# because the shell reads the trailing \r as part of the command. Keeping
# this file in the repo means `git clone` / `git checkout` always produces
# LF files on any machine, so run.sh works on the Pi without manual
# conversion (e.g. `sed -i 's/\r$//' run.sh`) after every edit.
* text=auto eol=lf

*.c   text eol=lf
*.h   text eol=lf
*.sh  text eol=lf
Makefile text eol=lf
*.md  text eol=lf
